reviews.review_text: Very Nice for the SPring '91 sound Go straight to the Shakedown and hear Atlanta uncork the spring fever of '91. As I remember this was a fun three night run. The Omni was a difficult place for good sound, so this AUD rates very high for anything I have heard from there. Nice Job. I enjoy this recording to remember the occasion, as I was there, but this is a nice recording of a fun time and you can enjoy it as well. I'll skip a play by play because I skip some of this set list on any recording, but overall a solid and perhaps top of the line performance for the tour.

Get it just for Stir it Up This is a quality audience tape with that "you are there" feel.  For the third and final time, the Dead played "Stir It Up".   It was instrumental only, and pretty sweet.  Keyboard work through the five minute song made it work.  Also good:  Queen Jane Approximately, Other One, Wharf Rat, and encore Quinn.  There seemed to be a bit of an audio issue at the very beginning (Shakedown), but it went away.  Worth a download.
